1
00:00:50,716 --> 00:00:54,812
[Doctor]
Um... you have no actual
medical training?

2
00:00:54,887 --> 00:00:59,950
No. I have kids.
Learned a lot right there.

3
00:01:00,026 --> 00:01:03,860
I mean, I've seen nurses
give my son throat cultures.

4
00:01:03,930 --> 00:01:08,230
What is it?
You stick a giant Q-Tip
down their throat and wait.

5
00:01:08,301 --> 00:01:12,635
Or a urinalysis, where you
take a dipstick to see whether
or not the white count's high.

6
00:01:12,705 --> 00:01:14,639
[Doctor]
Yes, I understand.
Yeah, yeah.

7
00:01:14,707 --> 00:01:18,404
I'm great with people.
You'd have to observe me
to know for sure,

8
00:01:18,478 --> 00:01:21,106
but you can trust me
on that.

9
00:01:21,180 --> 00:01:23,114
Yeah.
I'm an extremely
fast learner.

10
00:01:23,182 --> 00:01:26,777
You show me
something in a lab once,
and I've got it down.

11
00:01:26,853 --> 00:01:31,222
Mm-hmm.
I always wanted to go
to medical school.

12
00:01:31,290 --> 00:01:33,485
That was my first
interest really,

13
00:01:33,559 --> 00:01:37,495
but then I got married
and had a kid too young
and that kind of blew that.

14
00:01:37,563 --> 00:01:39,497
When I was first out
of high school,

15
00:01:39,565 --> 00:01:43,228
I got a job
with Fleuer Engineers
and Constructors in Irvine.

16
00:01:43,302 --> 00:01:46,465
I fell madly in love
with geology.

17
00:01:46,539 --> 00:01:49,702
Geology?
[Erin]
Yeah.

18
00:01:49,775 --> 00:01:51,709
I learned how to read maps.
I love maps.

19
00:01:51,777 --> 00:01:54,940
Yeah, but I lost my job
because...

20
00:01:55,014 --> 00:01:58,177
my boy came down
with the chicken pox,
had a 104 temperature,

21
00:01:58,251 --> 00:02:01,379
and my ex-husband
was useless, so...

22
00:02:01,454 --> 00:02:03,388
[Softly]
That didn't
really work out.

23
00:02:04,891 --> 00:02:06,825
Uh-huh.

24
00:02:09,428 --> 00:02:11,362
You got
a really nice office.

25
00:02:14,667 --> 00:02:17,329
Thanks.

26
00:02:19,839 --> 00:02:22,171
Look...

27
00:02:53,372 --> 00:02:55,306
Aw, fuck.

28
00:02:55,374 --> 00:02:57,308
[Sighs]

29
00:03:01,947 --> 00:03:05,439
- [Nail Break]
- Goddamn it.

30
00:03:09,755 --> 00:03:11,689
[Sighs]

31
00:03:22,134 --> 00:03:24,068
[Starts Engine]

32
00:03:45,623 --> 00:03:47,682
Good morning,
Mr. Masry.
Good morning,
Rosalind.

33
00:03:47,759 --> 00:03:50,785
How are you doing today?
Fine, thanks.
And you?

34
00:03:50,862 --> 00:03:52,853
Very well.
Thank you for asking.

35
00:03:52,931 --> 00:03:54,865
Good morning.

36
00:03:55,934 --> 00:03:57,902
Good morning.

37
00:03:59,971 --> 00:04:02,701
How ya doing?
Hi, Donald.

38
00:04:02,774 --> 00:04:05,902
[Brenda]
Did you see it last night?
I was out, but I taped it.

39
00:04:05,977 --> 00:04:09,572
Don't tell me what happens.
It was so good.
Your 9:00's here already.

40
00:04:18,456 --> 00:04:22,017
Remind me.
Erin Brockovich.

41
00:04:22,093 --> 00:04:24,027
Car accident.
Not her fault, she says.

42
00:04:25,864 --> 00:04:28,025
She was referred.

43
00:04:31,769 --> 00:04:33,703
Yeah.
All right?

44
00:04:33,771 --> 00:04:35,671
Erin, hi.

45
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:37,833
Hi.
[Closes Door]
Ed Masry.

46
00:04:37,909 --> 00:04:40,207
Sorry you had to wait.

47
00:04:40,278 --> 00:04:44,374
That's okay.
Here, sit, sit.
Sit down, sit down.

48
00:04:52,323 --> 00:04:55,781
Thank you.

49
00:04:55,860 --> 00:04:58,090
Oh.

50
00:04:58,162 --> 00:05:01,222
I never thought just standing
could take it out of you,

51
00:05:01,299 --> 00:05:03,324
but ever since
that shithead hit me,

52
00:05:03,401 --> 00:05:05,335
I feel like my whole body's
put together wrong.

53
00:05:05,403 --> 00:05:07,837
You poor thing.

54
00:05:07,906 --> 00:05:10,841
Uh, did anyone ask
if you wanted coffee?

55
00:05:10,909 --> 00:05:14,345
Yeah. I'm fine.
[Clears Throat]
[Ed] Good.

56
00:05:14,412 --> 00:05:19,111
Listen, whoever did this to you
made one hell of a mistake,

57
00:05:19,183 --> 00:05:22,778
and, you and me,
we're gonna make him pay for it.

58
00:05:25,890 --> 00:05:30,384
So, uh, why don't you tell me
what happened?

59
00:05:30,461 --> 00:05:34,261
I was pulling out real slow
and, out of nowhere,

60
00:05:34,332 --> 00:05:39,201
his Jaguar comes
racing around the corner
like a bat out of hell.

61
00:05:39,270 --> 00:05:43,764
They took some bone
from my hip and put it
in my neck.

62
00:05:43,841 --> 00:05:45,775
I don't have insurance,

63
00:05:45,843 --> 00:05:50,109
so I'm about $ 17,000
in debt right now.

64
00:05:50,181 --> 00:05:54,948
I couldn't take pain killers
'cause they made me too groggy
to take care of my kids.

65
00:05:55,019 --> 00:05:58,079
Matthew's eight
and Katie's almost six...

66
00:05:58,156 --> 00:06:01,216
and Beth's just nine months.

67
00:06:01,292 --> 00:06:04,557
I just want to be a good mom,
a nice person,

68
00:06:04,629 --> 00:06:06,722
a decent citizen.

69
00:06:06,798 --> 00:06:08,993
I just want to take good care
of my kids, you know?

70
00:06:09,067 --> 00:06:12,901
Yeah.
Yeah, I know.

71
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:19,736
Seventeen thousand in debt?
[Sighs]

72
00:06:19,811 --> 00:06:22,336
Is your ex-husband
helping out?
Which one?

73
00:06:24,816 --> 00:06:29,082
There's more than one?
Yeah, there's two.
Why?

74
00:06:33,925 --> 00:06:38,191
So, you must have been feeling
pretty desperate that afternoon.

75
00:06:38,262 --> 00:06:39,854
What's your point?

76
00:06:39,931 --> 00:06:42,525
[Attorney]
Broke, three kids,
no job.

77
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:45,865
- A doctor in a Jaguar must have
looked like a good meal ticket.
- Objection.

78
00:06:45,937 --> 00:06:47,632
[Judge]
Sustained.
What? He hit me.

79
00:06:47,705 --> 00:06:51,801
- So you say.
- He came tearing around
the corner, out of control!

80
00:06:51,876 --> 00:06:56,506
An E.R. Doctor,
who spends his day saving lives,
was the one out of control?

81
00:06:56,581 --> 00:07:00,950
That asshole smashed in
my fucking neck.

82
00:07:01,019 --> 00:07:03,544
[Spectators Murmuring]

83
00:07:03,621 --> 00:07:05,680
Open and shut.
Open and fucking shut!

84
00:07:05,757 --> 00:07:07,691
That is exactly
the kind of language
that lost the case.

85
00:07:07,759 --> 00:07:11,126
It was over long before that.
I told you the questions
might get personal.

86
00:07:11,195 --> 00:07:13,356
No, you told me
I'd be set!
I never said that.

87
00:07:13,431 --> 00:07:15,524
You told me
I had a good shot.
I had no shot!

88
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,966
Let's try
and settle down here.
Fuck "settle down"!

89
00:07:18,036 --> 00:07:21,631
I've got $ 74 in the bank.
I can't afford
to settle down.

90
00:07:21,706 --> 00:07:23,707
I'm sorry, Erin.

91
00:07:25,308 --> 00:07:27,503
Do they teach lawyers
to apologize?

92
00:07:27,577 --> 00:07:29,841
Because you suck at it.

93
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:07,309
Hello? Hi.
Hi, Erin.

94
00:08:07,384 --> 00:08:09,875
You've come so soon.
Yeah.

95
00:08:09,953 --> 00:08:12,854
Oh, were you
a good girl, huh?

96
00:08:12,923 --> 00:08:15,221
You're my little baby.
[Coughs]

97
00:08:15,292 --> 00:08:18,022
What is that,
a little cough?
She's got a little cough.

98
00:08:18,094 --> 00:08:21,757
I sat in the steam with her
to try to loosen it up, but...

99
00:08:21,831 --> 00:08:25,096
I think I've got
some cough medicine.
Ah, bueno.

100
00:08:25,168 --> 00:08:29,434
Um, listen... I didn't want
to tell you before,
Yeah?

101
00:08:29,506 --> 00:08:31,736
You know,
with your worries.
What?

102
00:08:31,808 --> 00:08:35,539
My daughter
bought a big house
with a room for me.

103
00:08:35,612 --> 00:08:37,546
I'm moving in with her.

104
00:08:37,614 --> 00:08:39,548
When?
Next week.

105
00:08:39,616 --> 00:08:42,813
Next week?
I know,
but it's good for me.

106
00:08:42,886 --> 00:08:47,090
Now I can help my daughter
take care of my grandkids.
And it's good for you too.

107
00:08:47,223 --> 00:08:50,249
Now you have money,
you can hire a good baby-sitter,
eh?

108
00:08:50,326 --> 00:08:52,692
Not the old lady
next door.

109
00:08:52,762 --> 00:08:54,696
Thanks.

110
00:08:55,565 --> 00:08:59,763
[Boy Yelling]
Matthew?

111
00:08:59,836 --> 00:09:02,566
Katie, you back here?
[Katie]
Yeah.

112
00:09:02,638 --> 00:09:04,572
Okay, come on in,
would you?

113
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:08,235
[Laughing]

114
00:09:08,311 --> 00:09:11,712
[Erin]
Hey, get in the house.
No dripping.

115
00:09:11,781 --> 00:09:13,806
[Both]
Okay.

116
00:09:16,219 --> 00:09:20,815
Sweetie, please,
don't get sick on me. Please.

117
00:09:25,862 --> 00:09:29,525
[Cooing]
[Crying]

118
00:09:29,599 --> 00:09:31,533
Let's fix
some dinner.

119
00:09:31,601 --> 00:09:34,035
[Crying Continues]

120
00:09:38,975 --> 00:09:42,467
[Erin Turns On Faucet]
Look at the water.

121
00:09:42,545 --> 00:09:44,979
[Continues Crying]

122
00:09:46,416 --> 00:09:48,384
[Turns Water Off]

123
00:09:49,586 --> 00:09:51,850
[Gasps, Drops Pan]
[Screaming]

124
00:09:51,921 --> 00:09:55,948
Damn it.
I'm sorry.
[Crying]

125
00:09:56,025 --> 00:09:57,993
[Continues Crying]

126
00:09:58,061 --> 00:10:03,089
Matthew! Katie!
We're going out.

127
00:10:05,201 --> 00:10:07,294
You kids go ahead
and order.

128
00:10:07,370 --> 00:10:10,396
Okay, I'm gonna have
a cheeseburger deluxe
with a Coke.

129
00:10:10,473 --> 00:10:12,566
Okay.

130
00:10:12,642 --> 00:10:15,475
Mommy, can I have
a cheeseburger deluxe...

131
00:10:15,545 --> 00:10:17,672
with no cheese
and no bread?

132
00:10:17,747 --> 00:10:20,716
- Did you get that?
- Yes.

133
00:10:20,783 --> 00:10:25,516
And she will have
a cup of chicken broth
and a few crackers, please.

134
00:10:25,588 --> 00:10:29,752
And for you?
Okay.
Just a cup of coffee.

135
00:10:29,826 --> 00:10:33,922
Mommy, you're not eating?
Well, my lawyer took me out
to a fancy lunch to celebrate,

136
00:10:33,997 --> 00:10:35,931
and I'm still stuffed.

137
00:10:35,999 --> 00:10:37,933
How about that?
[Laughing]

138
00:10:46,976 --> 00:10:48,910
[Coughs]

139
00:10:56,986 --> 00:10:59,921
[Beth Crying]

140
00:11:18,841 --> 00:11:21,401
I'm calling about the job ad
in the paper.

141
00:11:21,477 --> 00:11:23,877
Yes, I'm calling
about the job ad.

142
00:11:23,947 --> 00:11:26,745
Great personality, good voice.

143
00:11:26,816 --> 00:11:28,909
I don't have any actual
sales experience.

144
00:11:28,985 --> 00:11:32,546
I don't really have a resume,
but I can...

145
00:11:32,622 --> 00:11:35,056
No, I don't have
any computer skills, but...

146
00:11:35,124 --> 00:11:40,084
Oh. Well, I thought
it was the local store.

147
00:11:40,163 --> 00:11:42,996
Okay. Thanks anyway.

148
00:11:43,066 --> 00:11:46,661
Okay, bye.
[Hangs Up Receiver]

149
00:11:49,238 --> 00:11:52,332
[Clears Throat]
Ed Masry, please.

150
00:11:52,408 --> 00:11:54,638
Yes, I'm holding for Ed Masry.

151
00:11:54,711 --> 00:11:56,406
Is he ever in the office?

152
00:11:56,479 --> 00:11:59,073
No, but I've called
about a dozen times.

153
00:11:59,148 --> 00:12:00,945
Yes, I'd like
to leave another message.

154
00:12:01,017 --> 00:12:04,817
Brockovich.
B-r-o-c-k-o-v-i-c-h.

155
00:12:04,887 --> 00:12:08,584
I'm a client.
I want him to call me.
It's as simple as that.

156
00:12:12,929 --> 00:12:15,727
Okay.
[Sighs]

157
00:12:27,543 --> 00:12:31,377
[Gasps]
Goddamn it!

158
00:12:31,447 --> 00:12:34,814
Brenda!
Brenda!
Yeah?

159
00:12:34,884 --> 00:12:38,911
Who put that there?
Those are the files
you asked for.

160
00:12:38,988 --> 00:12:41,286
I didn't ask for you
to put it in the middle
of the floor.

161
00:12:41,357 --> 00:12:43,325
I mean, look at me.
Get a towel, will ya?

162
00:12:43,393 --> 00:12:45,327
Hey. Hey.

163
00:12:47,263 --> 00:12:50,357
What's she doing here?
Who?

164
00:12:53,469 --> 00:12:57,064
Donald.

165
00:12:57,140 --> 00:13:00,940
What's she doing here?
She works here.

166
00:13:13,723 --> 00:13:17,284
Erin, how's it going?

167
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,828
You never
called me back.
I left messages.

168
00:13:19,896 --> 00:13:21,921
You did?
Well, I didn't know that.

169
00:13:21,998 --> 00:13:26,901
Donald seems to think you...
There's two things that
aggravate me, Mr. Masry:

170
00:13:26,969 --> 00:13:29,335
Being ignored
and being lied to.

171
00:13:29,405 --> 00:13:31,839
I never lied.
You told me
things would be fine.

172
00:13:31,908 --> 00:13:33,842
They're not.
I trusted you.

173
00:13:33,910 --> 00:13:37,209
I'm sorry about that.
I am.
I don't need pity.
I need a paycheck.

174
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:40,681
I've looked, but when
you've spent the past
six years raising babies,

175
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:43,344
it's real hard to convince
someone to give you a job
that pays worth a damn.

176
00:13:43,419 --> 00:13:47,515
Are you getting every word
of this, honey, or am I
talking too fast for you?

177
00:13:47,590 --> 00:13:49,524
[Ed]
I'm sorry
about that.

178
00:13:49,592 --> 00:13:52,356
I really am, but we have
a full staff right now...
Bullshit!

179
00:13:52,428 --> 00:13:55,727
If you had a full staff,
this office would return
a client's damn phone call.

180
00:13:55,798 --> 00:13:59,859
I'm smart,
I'm hard-working,
and I'll do anything,

181
00:13:59,936 --> 00:14:01,870
and I'm not leaving here
without a job.

182
00:14:14,917 --> 00:14:17,408
[Softly]
Don't make me beg.

183
00:14:17,487 --> 00:14:21,218
If it doesn't work out,
fire me.

184
00:14:21,290 --> 00:14:23,224
Don't make me beg.

185
00:14:29,332 --> 00:14:31,994
No benefits.

186
00:14:34,270 --> 00:14:38,036
What we do in here
is file all the cases.

187
00:14:38,107 --> 00:14:41,634
That way, at any time,
we can tell the status
of a file.

188
00:14:41,711 --> 00:14:44,407
You know,
where it is in the office,
stuff like that.

189
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:48,177
Here's where we
organize all the files
alphabetically.

190
00:14:48,251 --> 00:14:52,517
Simple enough.
Okay.
Here's your desk.

191
00:14:52,588 --> 00:14:55,216
Come with me.
I want to show you
where the Xerox machine is.

192
00:14:55,291 --> 00:14:57,851
Everybody has a code,
and you need to know about that.

193
00:14:57,927 --> 00:15:00,361
Do I get to pick
my own code?
We'll see.

194
00:15:03,266 --> 00:15:05,826
[Erin]
Mr. Masry?
Yeah?

195
00:15:05,902 --> 00:15:08,962
I was wondering,
can you tell me who I talk to...

196
00:15:09,038 --> 00:15:12,201
about maybe getting
an advance on my paycheck,
just for the weekend?

197
00:15:12,275 --> 00:15:17,770
Rosalind's the office manager.
She handles the payroll
and petty cash.

198
00:15:19,515 --> 00:15:23,542
But she's gone already.
She leaves early on Fridays.

199
00:15:27,256 --> 00:15:30,123
Okay. Thank you.
Oh, for Pete's sake,
here, here.

200
00:15:33,029 --> 00:15:35,463
I've only got hundreds.

201
00:15:37,934 --> 00:15:40,926
Here.
[Clears Throat]

202
00:15:41,003 --> 00:15:43,198
I don't want your money,
Mr. Masry.

203
00:15:43,272 --> 00:15:47,140
Where do you think
your paycheck comes from?
Here.

204
00:15:47,210 --> 00:15:50,008
Have a good weekend.
Thank you.

205
00:15:50,079 --> 00:15:53,480
See you.
[Employees]
See you. Good night.

206
00:15:53,549 --> 00:15:55,483
[Ed]
See you Monday.

207
00:16:06,395 --> 00:16:10,559
Hey. Hi, my sweetie.
Hello. [Kisses]

208
00:16:10,633 --> 00:16:13,568
How are you?
Matthew? Katie?

209
00:16:13,636 --> 00:16:17,504
Hey, Mom.
Hi, sweetie.
Come on.

210
00:16:17,573 --> 00:16:19,837
How are you?
Thanks a lot.

211
00:16:19,909 --> 00:16:22,244
You're welcome.

212
00:16:25,046 --> 00:16:28,140
[Kisses]

213
00:16:34,823 --> 00:16:36,757
[Kisses]

214
00:16:48,870 --> 00:16:52,237
[Engine Revving]

215
00:16:52,307 --> 00:16:54,639
[Revving Continues]

216
00:16:54,709 --> 00:16:58,110
[Revving
Continues]
Hey!

217
00:16:58,179 --> 00:17:01,410
[Revving
Engine]
Hey!

218
00:17:01,483 --> 00:17:03,917
[Continues
Revving Engine]

219
00:17:03,985 --> 00:17:07,148
Hey!
Hello.

220
00:17:07,222 --> 00:17:09,952
What are you doing
making all that goddamn noise?

221
00:17:10,025 --> 00:17:12,960
Well, uh, I don't know.

222
00:17:13,028 --> 00:17:14,962
We were just
introducing ourselves
to the neighborhood, I guess.

223
00:17:15,030 --> 00:17:17,658
Well, I'm the neighbors.

224
00:17:17,732 --> 00:17:20,462
There, we're introduced,
so shut the fuck up.

225
00:17:20,535 --> 00:17:23,231
[Chuckling]
Hey, hey.

226
00:17:23,305 --> 00:17:26,741
Hold on there.
Let's start over,
okay?

227
00:17:26,808 --> 00:17:28,742
My name's George.
What's yours?

228
00:17:28,810 --> 00:17:33,577
Just think of me as the person
next door who likes it quiet.

229
00:17:33,648 --> 00:17:35,582
Hey, come on.
Don't be like that.

230
00:17:35,650 --> 00:17:37,845
Hell, we live next door
to each other.
I feel bad.

231
00:17:37,919 --> 00:17:40,854
I feel terrible. I'm sorry.
Will you accept my apology?

232
00:17:40,922 --> 00:17:44,187
