580
00:42:56,667 --> 00:42:59,363
[Doorbell Chimes]

581
00:42:59,436 --> 00:43:02,735
Maybe that's Ed McMahon.
Let's go see.

582
00:43:08,879 --> 00:43:10,506
Wrong Ed.

583
00:43:10,581 --> 00:43:12,879
I'm sorry?
What are you doing here?

584
00:43:12,950 --> 00:43:16,977
I had an interesting call
this afternoon
from Dr. Frankel...

585
00:43:17,054 --> 00:43:19,488
from UCLA.
Oh, yeah?

586
00:43:19,556 --> 00:43:23,890
He wanted you to know
that the legal limit
for hexavalent chromium...

587
00:43:23,961 --> 00:43:28,796
is.05 parts per million.

588
00:43:28,866 --> 00:43:32,563
And the rate you mentioned,
.58,

589
00:43:32,636 --> 00:43:34,570
it could be responsible
for the cancers...

590
00:43:34,638 --> 00:43:39,302
in that family
you asked about,
the Jensens.

591
00:43:39,376 --> 00:43:42,470
Well, wasn't that
nice of him?

592
00:43:42,546 --> 00:43:44,707
Isn't it funny
how some people go out
of their way to help people...

593
00:43:44,781 --> 00:43:46,715
and others just fire them?

594
00:43:46,783 --> 00:43:50,879
Look, I'm sorry.
You were gone. I assumed
you were off having fun.

595
00:43:50,954 --> 00:43:54,822
Oh, and why the hell
would you assume that?
I don't know.

596
00:43:54,892 --> 00:43:58,157
Maybe you look like someone
who has a lot of fun.
Oh.

597
00:43:58,228 --> 00:44:01,129
So, by that standard, I should
assume you never get laid?

598
00:44:03,700 --> 00:44:06,260
