to offer the Jensens
$250,000 for their home.

702
00:50:36,493 --> 00:50:38,484
[Scoffs]
Two hundred and fifty thousand?

703
00:50:38,561 --> 00:50:42,224
In terms of land value
out in Hinkley,

704
00:50:42,299 --> 00:50:45,097
Mr. Masry, we feel that's
a more than fair price.

705
00:50:45,168 --> 00:50:48,035
How about in terms
of medical expenses?

706
00:50:48,104 --> 00:50:50,129
Two hundred and fifty thousand
isn't gonna come close...

707
00:50:50,206 --> 00:50:52,800
to what this family's gonna have
to spend on doctors.

708
00:50:54,577 --> 00:50:57,603
I understand they've
had a bad run of luck
healthwise.

709
00:50:57,681 --> 00:51:01,139
They have my sympathies,
but that's not PG&E's fault.

710
00:51:01,217 --> 00:51:03,082
You're kidding,
right?

711
00:51:04,854 --> 00:51:06,845
Look at these readings.

712
00:51:06,923 --> 00:51:10,916
PG&E's own technicians
documented...

713
00:51:10,994 --> 00:51:13,462
toxic levels
of hexavalent chromium...

714
00:51:13,530 --> 00:51:16,624
in those wells
on numerous occasions.

715
00:51:16,700 --> 00:51:18,964
Everything
the Jensens
have had...

716
00:51:19,035 --> 00:51:22,232
is proven reaction
to exposure to hexavalent
chromium.

717
00:51:22,305 --> 00:51:25,035
They have had...

718
00:51:25,108 --> 00:51:27,076
They have had...

719
00:51:29,579 --> 00:51:31,774
Breast cysts,
uterine cancer,

720
00:51:31,848 --> 00:51:34,043
Hodgkin's disease,
immune deficiencies,

721
00:51:34,117 --> 00:51:38,213
asthma, chronic nosebleeds...
A million things could have
caused those problems.

722
00:51:38,288 --> 00:51:42,725
Poor diet, bad genes,
irresponsible lifestyle.

723
00:51:42,792 --> 00:51:44,851
Our offer is final,
and it's more than fair.

724
00:51:44,928 --> 00:51:48,625
Wait a minute.
I thought we were
negotiating here.

725
00:51:51,601 --> 00:51:55,799
Two hundred and fifty thousand
dollars is all I'm authorized
to offer.

726
00:51:57,874 --> 00:52:00,468
I'll present your offer
to my clients.

727
00:52:00,543 --> 00:52:03,034
I doubt
they'll accept.
Mr. Masry...

728
00:52:04,814 --> 00:52:06,748
before you go off
on some crusade,

729
00:52:06,816 --> 00:52:09,546
you might want
to remember who it is
you're dealing with here.

730
00:52:09,619 --> 00:52:13,248
PG&E's a $28-billion
corporation.

731
00:52:13,323 --> 00:52:16,759
$28 billion!

732
00:52:16,826 --> 00:52:19,192
I didn't know
it was that much!

733
00:52:19,262 --> 00:52:23,221
Wow! 28 billion!

734
00:52:23,299 --> 00:52:25,995
[Sighs]
Holy cow!

735
00:52:26,069 --> 00:52:28,333
At least
they made an offer.
That wasn't an offer.

736
00:52:28,405 --> 00:52:31,397
A million would have
been an offer.

737
00:52:31,474 --> 00:52:34,034
They sent a mail clerk down
to jerk me off, waste my time!

738
00:52:34,110 --> 00:52:37,409
- Why would they do that?
- Because they can.

739
00:52:37,480 --> 00:52:41,177
You heard what that kid said.
They have $28 billion
at their disposal!

740
00:52:41,251 --> 00:52:43,742
- They can afford to waste
all the time in the world.
- And you can't?

741
00:52:43,820 --> 00:52:46,345
- You think I'm made of money?
- What are you yelling
at me for?

742
00:52:46,423 --> 00:52:48,220
- Because I'm pissed off!
- Good!

743
00:52:48,291 --> 00:52:51,590
- Fuck you!
- Fuck you back!

744
00:52:52,962 --> 00:52:57,160
[Laughing]

745
00:52:57,233 --> 00:53:00,259
[Laughing Continues]

746
00:53:00,336 --> 00:53:03,703
[Continues Laughing]
I really hate you sometimes,
you know that?

747
00:53:03,773 --> 00:53:06,264
Ah, you love me.

748
00:53:06,342 --> 00:53:08,640
[Laughing Continues]

749
00:53:08,711 --> 00:53:12,238
[Footsteps Approaching]

750
00:53:12,315 --> 00:53:15,773
[Footsteps Continue]

751
00:53:18,154 --> 00:53:20,679
You've been reading
for hours.

752
00:53:20,757 --> 00:53:23,157
I'm a slow reader.

753
00:53:27,297 --> 00:53:32,132
[Footsteps Departing]

754
00:53:32,202 --> 00:53:34,438
[Door Closes]

755
00:53:36,606 --> 00:53:39,200
[Man]
Uh, Erin Brockovich?

756
00:53:44,781 --> 00:53:48,376
That's probably her
at that desk.

757
00:53:51,621 --> 00:53:53,555
Excuse me.

758
00:53:53,623 --> 00:53:56,592
Are you
Erin Brockovich?
Yeah.

759
00:53:56,660 --> 00:54:00,756
Uh, I'm Tom... Robinson.
This is my wife Mandy.

760
00:54:00,831 --> 00:54:04,460
Hi.
[Tom]
We used to live across
the street from the Jensens.

761
00:54:04,534 --> 00:54:07,059
I think you know Donna.
[Erin]
Yeah.

762
00:54:07,137 --> 00:54:11,267
Uh, PG&E bought our house
last year.

763
00:54:11,341 --> 00:54:15,903
[Tom]
The vets said they had
a bunch of tumors and stuff...

764
00:54:15,979 --> 00:54:20,609
and, you can see,
they couldn't really walk.

765
00:54:20,684 --> 00:54:22,743
How many were born
like this?

766
00:54:22,819 --> 00:54:27,415
Uh, 12 or 13
or so.
Yeah.

767
00:54:27,491 --> 00:54:31,587
When Donna told us about you
and what you told her
about the chromium,

768
00:54:31,661 --> 00:54:34,687
we figured
that might have something
to do with this too.

769
00:54:34,764 --> 00:54:38,860
Yeah, it might.
May I keep these?
Yes.

770
00:54:38,935 --> 00:54:42,268
Okay. Great.
Thank you so much.
I really appreciate it.

771
00:54:42,339 --> 00:54:46,070
Um...
There's something else too.

772
00:54:47,777 --> 00:54:51,645
What?
Um... this, uh...

773
00:54:51,715 --> 00:54:56,311
Um... well, uh...
Mandy here has had...

774
00:54:56,386 --> 00:54:58,320
five miscarriages.

775
00:54:58,388 --> 00:55:01,152
I'm so sorry.

776
00:55:01,224 --> 00:55:05,058
I figured it was
something I did...

777
00:55:05,128 --> 00:55:08,063
like when I smoked
marijuana maybe...

778
00:55:08,131 --> 00:55:10,725
or took
birth control pills.

779
00:55:10,800 --> 00:55:16,568
But then Donna said
you thought chromium might be
to blame for her problems.

780
00:55:16,640 --> 00:55:18,904
So I figured...

781
00:55:21,811 --> 00:55:23,745
maybe it wasn't just me.

782
00:55:31,855 --> 00:55:34,847
[Sighs]
Whoa.

783
00:55:34,925 --> 00:55:37,359
[Kissing]

784
00:55:40,230 --> 00:55:42,164
I have
to take a bath.

785
00:55:42,232 --> 00:55:46,191
You should go in.

786
00:55:46,269 --> 00:55:48,533
They're not asleep?

787
00:55:50,106 --> 00:55:52,040
[Sighs]

788
00:55:52,108 --> 00:55:54,372
Beth and Katie are.

789
00:56:00,617 --> 00:56:02,881
Hey.

790
00:56:09,292 --> 00:56:11,260
How was school?

791
00:56:11,328 --> 00:56:13,387
Fine.

792
00:56:13,463 --> 00:56:16,125
Did you do
your homework?
Yeah.

793
00:56:17,801 --> 00:56:19,735
Any problems?

794
00:56:30,981 --> 00:56:35,008
I know you're upset,
but... the way this job is,

795
00:56:35,085 --> 00:56:37,679
things come up
at the last minute;

796
00:56:37,754 --> 00:56:39,847
real important things
that I gotta deal with.

797
00:56:39,923 --> 00:56:41,857
Fine!

798
00:56:47,430 --> 00:56:51,366
Please don't be mad at me.
I'm doing this for us.

799
00:56:51,434 --> 00:56:55,370
I know it's hard for you
to understand, but...

800
00:56:56,940 --> 00:56:59,306
Don't you want Mommy
to be good at her job?

801
00:56:59,376 --> 00:57:02,209
Hmm?

802
00:57:06,449 --> 00:57:10,408
It's not like
I miss dinner all the time.
We all ate together last night.

803
00:57:10,487 --> 00:57:13,285
You were reading
the whole time.

804
00:57:18,962 --> 00:57:20,896
Okay.

805
00:57:26,970 --> 00:57:29,996
[Honking Horn]

806
00:57:36,145 --> 00:57:39,239
[Man]
You know, there's something
about this whole thing...

807
00:57:39,315 --> 00:57:41,806
I don't quite understand,
Mr. Masry.

808
00:57:41,884 --> 00:57:44,512
If PG&E messed
with our water,

809
00:57:44,587 --> 00:57:48,114
why would they bother
saying anything about it
to us at all?

810
00:57:48,190 --> 00:57:50,249
Why not just
keep quiet about it?

811
00:57:50,326 --> 00:57:52,692
To establish
a statute of limitations.

812
00:57:52,762 --> 00:57:55,356
In a case like this,
you only have one year...

813
00:57:55,431 --> 00:57:58,958
from the time you first learn
about the problem to file suit.

814
00:57:59,035 --> 00:58:01,435
So PG&E figures...

815
00:58:01,504 --> 00:58:05,634
we'll let the cat out
of the bag, tell the people
the water's not perfect,

816
00:58:05,708 --> 00:58:08,700
and if we can ride out the year
with no one suing,

817
00:58:08,778 --> 00:58:10,973
we'll be in the clear forever.

818
00:58:11,047 --> 00:58:13,481
But it was more than a year ago
that they told us.

819
00:58:13,549 --> 00:58:16,712
It's okay.
We're not suing.
Not yet.

820
00:58:16,786 --> 00:58:19,687
All we're doing is using
this information...

821
00:58:19,755 --> 00:58:23,816
to get you a real nice
purchase price
on your house...

822
00:58:23,893 --> 00:58:27,693
and, you two,
a comparable retroactive bonus
on your sale price.

823
00:58:27,763 --> 00:58:30,698
That way,
PG&E can still look good
to their shareholders...

824
00:58:30,766 --> 00:58:32,734
because they're not involved
in an ugly lawsuit.

825
00:58:32,802 --> 00:58:35,168
All they're doing
is buying a little property.

826
00:58:35,237 --> 00:58:40,140
It... doesn't say here
how much this thing
is gonna cost us.

827
00:58:40,209 --> 00:58:44,236
My fee is 40% of whatever
you get awarded.

828
00:58:53,322 --> 00:58:56,348
Boy, do I know
how you feel.

829
00:58:56,425 --> 00:59:01,021
The first time
I heard that number, I said,
"You've got to be kidding me.

830
00:59:01,097 --> 00:59:04,931
Forty goddamn percent?
I'm the one that's injured."
Erin...

831
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:09,198
"This joker sits at a desk,
and he wants to walk away
with almost half my reward?"

832
00:59:09,271 --> 00:59:11,398
Erin, can l...
But then...

833
00:59:11,474 --> 00:59:14,034
I asked him...

834
00:59:14,110 --> 00:59:16,874
what he makes
if I don't get anything.

835
00:59:16,946 --> 00:59:20,382
Then I don't
get anything either.

836
00:59:20,449 --> 00:59:22,781
[Erin]
Plus he's out
all the costs.

837
00:59:22,852 --> 00:59:27,289
So I realized...
he's taking a chance too.

838
00:59:35,965 --> 00:59:38,525
You got a pen, honey?

839
00:59:43,105 --> 00:59:45,039
Well, all right then.

840
00:59:47,977 --> 00:59:50,002
Oh, I made a bundt cake.

841
00:59:50,079 --> 00:59:52,047
Let me put on some coffee.
Who would like coffee and cake?

842
00:59:52,114 --> 00:59:55,277
I do.
Thanks, but we have
to be getting back.

843
00:59:56,552 --> 00:59:59,020
[Whispers]
Have a fucking
cup of coffee, Ed.

844
00:59:59,088 --> 01:00:01,556
Coffee will be great.
Thank you.

845
01:00:01,624 --> 01:00:03,558
[Donna]
All right.
I'll help you.

846
01:00:08,097 --> 01:00:11,032
My wife makes
really good bundt cake.

847
01:00:11,100 --> 01:00:14,203
I love bundt cake.

848
01:00:14,336 --> 01:00:16,361
[Water Hose Running]

849
01:00:16,438 --> 01:00:21,000
[Bob Linwood] Seems like
everybody in the family
ended up with a rash somehow.

850
01:00:21,076 --> 01:00:25,240
It also seemed like no matter
what we did for it,
it always came back.

851
01:00:25,314 --> 01:00:28,215
Over what kind
of period of time?

852
01:00:28,283 --> 01:00:30,877
Oh... a long time.
You know, years.

853
01:00:30,953 --> 01:00:35,481
Never did keep track of it.
Kids are sick.
Animals need to be fed.

854
01:00:35,557 --> 01:00:37,582
Just couldn't
get rid of it.
That's all.

855
01:00:37,659 --> 01:00:41,186
[Erin]
Well, Mrs. De Soto said...

856
01:00:41,263 --> 01:00:44,494
that she wasn't
exactly sure what you had.

857
01:00:44,566 --> 01:00:47,160
We know what it is.
It's gastro...

858
01:00:47,236 --> 01:00:49,466
Gastrointestinal cancer.
Cancer. Yeah.

859
01:00:49,538 --> 01:00:52,837
She got sick about...
nine months ago.
[Laura Ambrosino] Nine months ago.

860
01:00:52,908 --> 01:00:55,172
[Mike Ambrosino]
They operated on her
about six months ago.

861
01:00:55,244 --> 01:00:57,678
[Laura Ambrosino]
Mm-hmm. The intestine.
Right.

862
01:01:07,589 --> 01:01:11,992
Hi, I'm Erin...
I know who you are.
Donna called me.

863
01:01:12,060 --> 01:01:15,052
Oh.
Can I come in?

864
01:01:15,130 --> 01:01:18,896
I told Donna
we're not interested
in getting involved.

865
01:01:20,035 --> 01:01:21,969
Can I ask why?

866
01:01:22,037 --> 01:01:25,029
What's the point?

867
01:01:26,608 --> 01:01:30,339
Well, Donna told me
that you've been sick...

868
01:01:30,412 --> 01:01:34,041
and that your kids
were sick...
You people don't give a shit.

869
01:01:34,116 --> 01:01:36,641
Anything to get what you want.

870
01:01:44,593 --> 01:01:48,029
[Erin]
It's good of you to have me in
when I just stopped by.

871
01:01:48,096 --> 01:01:50,155
She's feeling
pretty good today.
She's doing well.

872
01:01:50,232 --> 01:01:55,067
Mike Ambrosino remembered he had
seen you folks at the hospital
from time to time.

873
01:01:55,137 --> 01:01:57,071
That's what
brought me out here.

874
01:01:57,139 --> 01:01:59,835
[Chuckles]
Yeah.
Yeah.

875
01:01:59,908 --> 01:02:02,536
We've been there
from time to time.
Yeah.

876
01:02:02,611 --> 01:02:06,604
And you... Wooftie.
Aren't you a beauty?
[Rita Daniels Laughs]

877
01:02:06,682 --> 01:02:09,344
You drive all
the boys crazy,
don't you?

878
01:02:09,418 --> 01:02:12,785
[Chuckling]
I can see it in your eyes.
You drive them wild.

879
01:02:12,854 --> 01:02:14,685
You do, don't you?

880
01:02:14,756 --> 01:02:18,522
You torture them.
It's good for them.

881
01:02:18,593 --> 01:02:22,461
Don't teach her anything
too early.
[Laughs]
Yeah.

882
01:02:22,531 --> 01:02:26,023
She can't wait
to get on her new dress.
Isn't that right?

883
01:02:26,101 --> 01:02:29,434
[Ted Daniels]
She wants to go back to school.
We're trying to do that...

884
01:02:29,504 --> 01:02:33,372
in the next couple months.
Yeah, get her out
of her nightgown.

885
01:02:33,442 --> 01:02:38,311
[Ted Daniels]
She's gonna do it.
She's gonna do it.

886
01:02:55,831 --> 01:02:58,994
Absolutely not.
That's crazy.
Why not?

887
01:02:59,067 --> 01:03:02,161
Because I said no.
The only reason PG&E's
even talking to us...

888
01:03:02,237 --> 01:03:05,001
is because
this is a quiet, little
real estate dispute.

889
01:03:05,073 --> 01:03:08,839
We add plaintiffs,
suddenly we're in the middle
or a toxic tort...

890
01:03:08,910 --> 01:03:11,845
with a statute problem
against a massive utility.

891
01:03:11,913 --> 01:03:14,074
No, thank you.
Okay.

892
01:03:14,149 --> 01:03:16,674
So I'll go
to Ted and Rita Daniels...

893
01:03:16,752 --> 01:03:19,016
two of the nicest people
you could ever hope to meet...

894
01:03:19,087 --> 01:03:22,352
who every single day watch
their little girl, Annabelle,
fight like a dog against cancer,

895
01:03:22,424 --> 01:03:25,689
and I'll tell them
we can't help them because...

896
01:03:25,761 --> 01:03:27,695
you just don't want
to work that hard.

897
01:03:27,763 --> 01:03:33,258
Work hard?
Let me tell you something.
I've worked all my life.

898
01:03:33,335 --> 01:03:35,565
I've built a firm
and managed to keep it alive...

899
01:03:35,637 --> 01:03:37,764
through lawsuits,
injunctions and evictions.

900
01:03:37,839 --> 01:03:40,865
I've survived
a quadruple bypass, cancer,

901
01:03:40,942 --> 01:03:43,706
being born with one kidney
and having diabetes.

902
01:03:43,779 --> 01:03:46,873
I've personally managed
to save a million dollars...

903
01:03:46,948 --> 01:03:49,610
over 30 years of getting
some clients ten times that.

904
01:03:49,684 --> 01:03:51,879
Don't tell me
I don't work hard.

905
01:03:51,953 --> 01:03:55,719
Don't tell me I haven't
earned the right to stop,
take a breath and enjoy life.

906
01:03:55,791 --> 01:03:58,487
And what the hell do you know
about any of this anyway?

907
01:03:58,560 --> 01:04:01,893
Something like this, Erin...
It could take forever.

908
01:04:01,963 --> 01:04:03,897
They're a huge corporation.

909
01:04:03,965 --> 01:04:06,559
They could bury us in paperwork
for the next 15 years.

910
01:04:06,635 --> 01:04:08,865
I'm just a guy
with a small, private firm!

911
01:04:08,937 --> 01:04:13,169
Who happens to know
they poisoned people
and lied about it.

912
01:04:13,241 --> 01:04:15,232
We can get these people.

913
01:04:15,310 --> 01:04:19,576
With a little effort,
I really think we can just
nail their asses to the wall.

914
01:04:19,648 --> 01:04:21,912
You do? With all
your legal expertise,
you believe that?

915
01:04:21,983 --> 01:04:24,918
Don't you ever just know?
You also "just know" where
the money's coming from?

916
01:04:24,986 --> 01:04:26,920
That's why most
of these cases settle:
Lack of money.

917
01:04:26,988 --> 01:04:30,082
Do you know
what toxicologists
and geology experts cost?

918
01:04:30,158 --> 01:04:32,422
We're looking
at 100 grand a month, easy.

919
01:04:32,494 --> 01:04:35,861
I've already made
a huge dent in my savings.
We'll figure it out.

