1143
01:20:09,394 --> 01:20:12,261
a complaint
on behalf of the residents
of Hinkley, California,

1144
01:20:12,330 --> 01:20:15,822
who have filed this lawsuit
against Pacific Gas
and Electric...

1145
01:20:15,901 --> 01:20:19,837
for damages, medical expenses
and personal trauma...

1146
01:20:19,905 --> 01:20:22,203
due to contamination
of the groundwater...

1147
01:20:22,274 --> 01:20:24,765
in their area
by the defendant.

1148
01:20:24,843 --> 01:20:27,835
And I have here
84 motions to strike...

1149
01:20:27,913 --> 01:20:31,212
and demurrers
submitted by representatives
of Pacific Gas and Electric,

1150
01:20:31,283 --> 01:20:36,311
each attacking the validity
of this complaint.

1151
01:20:36,388 --> 01:20:40,518
I have reviewed
all of the information
carefully.

1152
01:20:40,592 --> 01:20:43,026
I'm ready to give my decision.

1153
01:20:43,095 --> 01:20:46,326
Before I do, is there anything
anyone wants to say?

1154
01:20:46,398 --> 01:20:49,993
- No, Your Honor.
- No, Your Honor.

1155
01:20:50,068 --> 01:20:52,332
Very well.

1156
01:20:52,404 --> 01:20:54,497
In the matter of the plaintiffs
of Hinkley, California,

1157
01:20:54,573 --> 01:20:58,509
versus Pacific Gas and Electric,
it is the order of this court...

1158
01:20:58,577 --> 01:21:04,345
that each of the 84 motions
to strike and demurrers
are denied...

1159
01:21:04,416 --> 01:21:09,718
and the causes of action
against Pacific Gas and Electric
are upheld.

1160
01:21:09,788 --> 01:21:12,086
On a more personal note,

1161
01:21:12,157 --> 01:21:16,685
as a resident here in Barstow,
which is not far from Hinkley,

1162
01:21:16,762 --> 01:21:20,858
I am disturbed
by reference to evidence...

1163
01:21:20,932 --> 01:21:24,527
that suggests that not only
was hexavalent chromium used...

1164
01:21:24,603 --> 01:21:28,198
but that your clients
actually sent these residents...

1165
01:21:28,273 --> 01:21:32,505
pamphlets telling them
that it was good for them.

1166
01:21:33,779 --> 01:21:35,906
Tell your clients
they're going to trial.

1167
01:21:47,058 --> 01:21:50,858
[Erin]
Jesus, they look like
the Secret Service.

1168
01:21:50,929 --> 01:21:53,989
Intimidation.

1169
01:21:54,065 --> 01:21:57,330
Let the games begin.

1170
01:21:57,402 --> 01:21:59,666
Show them
into the conference room.

1171
01:22:01,907 --> 01:22:07,174
Donald, Anna,
I want to talk to you
for a minute.

1172
01:22:11,650 --> 01:22:14,312
[Ed]
Counselors.
Counselors.

1173
01:22:20,926 --> 01:22:22,917
Let's be honest here.

1174
01:22:22,994 --> 01:22:26,953
$20 million is more money
than these people
have ever dreamed of.

1175
01:22:27,032 --> 01:22:30,001
See, now that
pisses me off.

1176
01:22:30,068 --> 01:22:34,198
First of all,
since the demurrer, we have
more than 400 plaintiffs,

1177
01:22:34,272 --> 01:22:37,264
and, let's be honest,
we all know there
are more out there.

1178
01:22:37,342 --> 01:22:40,743
They may not be
the most sophisticated people,
but they do know how to divide.

1179
01:22:40,812 --> 01:22:43,178
$20 million isn't shit
when you split it between them.

1180
01:22:43,248 --> 01:22:45,148
Erin...
[Erin]
Second of all,

1181
01:22:45,217 --> 01:22:47,310
these people don't dream
about being rich.

1182
01:22:47,385 --> 01:22:50,821
They dream about being able
to watch their kids
swim in a pool...

1183
01:22:50,889 --> 01:22:54,188
without worrying they'll
have to have a hysterectomy
at the age of 20...

1184
01:22:54,259 --> 01:22:56,193
like Rosa Diaz,
a client of ours.

1185
01:22:56,261 --> 01:23:01,096
Or have their spine
deteriorate like Stan Bloom,
another client of ours.

1186
01:23:01,166 --> 01:23:04,829
So before you come back here
with another lame-ass offer,

1187
01:23:04,903 --> 01:23:09,272
I want you to think
real hard about what your
spine is worth, Mr. Walker.

1188
01:23:09,341 --> 01:23:12,833
Or what you might expect someone
to pay you for your uterus,
Ms. Sanchez.

1189
01:23:12,911 --> 01:23:15,004
Then you take out
your calculator,

1190
01:23:15,080 --> 01:23:17,310
and you multiply
that number by a hundred.

1191
01:23:17,382 --> 01:23:20,681
Anything less than that
is a waste of our time.

1192
01:23:22,921 --> 01:23:25,685
We had that water
brought in special
for you folks.

1193
01:23:25,757 --> 01:23:29,352
It came from a well
in Hinkley.

1194
01:23:29,427 --> 01:23:31,554
[Stifles Chuckle,
Clears Throat]

1195
01:23:44,276 --> 01:23:46,244
I think this meeting's over.

1196
01:23:46,311 --> 01:23:48,302
Damn right it is.

1197
01:24:17,241 --> 01:24:20,335
[Door Opens, Closes]

1198
01:24:25,483 --> 01:24:30,443
What the fuck, George?
Did a bomb blow up?
You letting the kids run wild?

1199
01:24:39,263 --> 01:24:41,356
What's that?

1200
01:24:51,442 --> 01:24:54,377
I saw them
in a mall one day.

1201
01:24:54,445 --> 01:24:59,542
I said, "Damn...
those would look good
on those beautiful ears."

1202
01:25:01,952 --> 01:25:04,887
So I bought them and I said,
"Next time Erin does something
nice or says something nice...

1203
01:25:04,955 --> 01:25:07,014
I'll surprise her with them."

1204
01:25:08,459 --> 01:25:12,054
You know how long ago
that was?

1205
01:25:12,129 --> 01:25:14,461
Six months ago.

1206
01:25:16,801 --> 01:25:20,897
I'm sorry...
So what
I'm thinking is...

1207
01:25:23,708 --> 01:25:27,735
Erin, either you gotta
find a different job
or a different guy.

1208
01:25:29,880 --> 01:25:31,905
I mean...

1209
01:25:31,982 --> 01:25:36,681
there may be many men
out there who don't mind
being the maid...

1210
01:25:36,754 --> 01:25:39,416
and getting nothing in return,
but I sure ain't one of them.

1211
01:25:41,425 --> 01:25:43,825
I can't leave my job, George.

1212
01:25:43,894 --> 01:25:45,828
Yes, you can.

1213
01:25:45,896 --> 01:25:48,364
You can just quit.
People do it all the time.

1214
01:25:48,432 --> 01:25:52,698
How can you ask me to do that?

1215
01:25:52,770 --> 01:25:55,864
This job...

1216
01:25:55,940 --> 01:26:00,707
For the first time in my life,
I got people respecting me.

1217
01:26:00,778 --> 01:26:05,044
Up in Hinkley,
I walk into a room
and everybody shuts up...

1218
01:26:05,116 --> 01:26:07,050
to hear if
I got something to say.

1219
01:26:07,118 --> 01:26:10,383
I never had that before, ever.

1220
01:26:10,454 --> 01:26:13,184
Please, don't ask me
to give it up.

1221
01:26:13,257 --> 01:26:15,191
What about what
your kids are giving up?

1222
01:26:15,259 --> 01:26:19,662
I'm doing more
for my kids now than I did
living with my parents.

1223
01:26:19,730 --> 01:26:21,664
One day,
they'll understand that.

1224
01:26:21,732 --> 01:26:24,530
- What about me?
- What about you?

1225
01:26:24,602 --> 01:26:27,127
[Scoffs]

1226
01:26:28,806 --> 01:26:31,240
You think either one of the men
who gave me those children...

1227
01:26:31,308 --> 01:26:34,675
asked me what I wanted
before he walked away?

1228
01:26:34,745 --> 01:26:38,340
All I've ever done
is bend my life around...

1229
01:26:38,416 --> 01:26:40,850
what men decide they need.

1230
01:26:40,918 --> 01:26:44,149
Well, not now.
I'm sorry. I won't do it.

1231
01:26:44,221 --> 01:26:47,190
Well... Erin, I'm not them.

1232
01:26:47,258 --> 01:26:51,695
So... what more do I have to do
to prove that to you?

1233
01:26:51,762 --> 01:26:55,027
Stay.

1234
01:27:09,447 --> 01:27:13,884
What for? Huh?

1235
01:27:13,951 --> 01:27:16,044
You got a raise.

1236
01:27:16,120 --> 01:27:18,350
You can afford day care.
You don't need me.

1237
01:27:31,836 --> 01:27:35,499
[Radio Announcer]
Let's take a look
at the five-day forecast.

1238
01:27:35,573 --> 01:27:38,406
This is what you can expect
in the high desert.

1239
01:27:38,476 --> 01:27:41,843
Ninety-three the high tomorrow.
The overnight low will be 60.

1240
01:27:41,912 --> 01:27:44,403
Twenty percent chance of showers
for most of the afternoon.

1241
01:27:44,482 --> 01:27:50,148
[Announcer Continues,
Indistinct]

1242
01:27:54,091 --> 01:27:56,025
[Turns Off Radio]

1243
01:28:03,100 --> 01:28:05,034
[Erin]
Hi.

1244
01:28:15,279 --> 01:28:17,213
Thank you.

1245
01:28:20,217 --> 01:28:24,779
[Erin]
We can get them, Pamela.
We can.

1246
01:28:24,855 --> 01:28:27,722
I don't want to feel it
all over again...

1247
01:28:27,791 --> 01:28:30,555
and then not have it
come out right.

1248
01:28:32,129 --> 01:28:35,292
I don't know
if I could handle that,

1249
01:28:35,366 --> 01:28:38,494
put the kids through that.

1250
01:28:38,569 --> 01:28:40,537
The thing is,
it doesn't matter...

1251
01:28:40,604 --> 01:28:42,834
whether you win, lose
or draw here.

1252
01:28:42,907 --> 01:28:45,000
You were lied to.
You're sick,

1253
01:28:45,075 --> 01:28:48,511
and your kids are sick
because of those lies.

1254
01:28:50,581 --> 01:28:53,516
If for no other reason,
you have to come together...

1255
01:28:53,584 --> 01:28:56,382
to stand up in a courtroom
and say that.

1256
01:29:01,926 --> 01:29:04,861
I'd bring the kids
into the hospital...

1257
01:29:04,929 --> 01:29:08,592
with towels soaked
from their nosebleeds.

1258
01:29:11,535 --> 01:29:17,303
They called county services
because they assumed the kids
were being abused.

1259
01:29:21,245 --> 01:29:25,204
[Erin]
Am I gonna get the best
behavior in the office?

1260
01:29:25,282 --> 01:29:28,046
[Matthew]
No.
What's with the attitude?

1261
01:29:28,118 --> 01:29:32,214
I just need cool.
I need quiet. Okay?

1262
01:29:32,289 --> 01:29:34,917
Hello? Am I alone
in the car? Yes?

1263
01:29:34,992 --> 01:29:38,155
I said, "We'll see."
I don't want to talk about it.

1264
01:29:38,228 --> 01:29:41,163
All the other moms
gave permission.
I don't care.

1265
01:29:41,231 --> 01:29:46,168
So when can I get
a frickin' answer?
Don't talk to me like that!

1266
01:29:46,236 --> 01:29:49,000
Randy's mom
said yes right away.
Goddamn it, Matthew!

1267
01:29:49,073 --> 01:29:52,008
Randy's mom doesn't work,
and Randy's dad
did not leave her.

1268
01:29:52,076 --> 01:29:57,912
So figuring out who can take who
to roller hockey is probably
easier at Randy's house.

1269
01:29:57,982 --> 01:30:00,507
[Erin Sighs]
[Rosalind]
Hey, Erin.

1270
01:30:00,584 --> 01:30:02,518
Hey.
Okay.

1271
01:30:02,586 --> 01:30:06,352
I'll be as quick as I can.
Matthew, can you watch
your sister?

1272
01:30:06,423 --> 01:30:10,018
Matthew?
All right, fine.
Come here, Beth.

1273
01:30:10,094 --> 01:30:13,689
Can I come
with you?
No, baby.
I'll just be a second.

1274
01:30:13,764 --> 01:30:16,198
[Clears Throat]

1275
01:30:17,768 --> 01:30:22,102
[Phone Ringing]

1276
01:30:49,333 --> 01:30:52,325
[Ed]
Thank you. I'm only sorry
you didn't get to meet Erin.

1277
01:30:52,403 --> 01:30:54,997
[Man]
I will. We have
a lot of work to do together.

1278
01:30:55,072 --> 01:30:57,836
[Ed]
Yep. Okay.
Thanks for coming over.

1279
01:30:57,908 --> 01:31:00,638
Erin, I was just talking
about you. This is our new
partner, Kurt Potter.

1280
01:31:00,711 --> 01:31:02,645
He'll be handling
Hinkley now.

1281
01:31:02,713 --> 01:31:05,682
[Sighs]
I see what you mean
about a secret weapon.

1282
01:31:05,749 --> 01:31:10,015
It's great to meet you.
You've done a fabulous job.
I'll be seeing you.

1283
01:31:10,087 --> 01:31:13,352
Thanks.
I appreciate you
coming over.
Yep.

1284
01:31:19,229 --> 01:31:21,163
[Opening Envelope]

1285
01:31:24,268 --> 01:31:27,362
- What?
- "Our new partner"?

1286
01:31:27,438 --> 01:31:29,929
When was
I gonna hear about this,
in the monthly newsletter?

1287
01:31:30,007 --> 01:31:34,137
Just listen.
Did I ever tell you
about that airline case?

1288
01:31:34,211 --> 01:31:36,475
What the fuck
are you talking about?

1289
01:31:36,547 --> 01:31:39,448
A few years back
I was trying this
airline case,

1290
01:31:39,516 --> 01:31:41,643
and I got my ass kicked
by this guy.

1291
01:31:41,719 --> 01:31:44,153
He just buried me in paper.
Brutal.

1292
01:31:44,221 --> 01:31:46,746
This guy was the toughest mother
I'd ever been up against.

1293
01:31:46,824 --> 01:31:50,487
- Make a point.
- It was Kurt Potter.

1294
01:31:50,561 --> 01:31:52,495
When we got the PG&E decision
from the judge,

1295
01:31:52,563 --> 01:31:54,656
I called him
and asked him to partner.

1296
01:31:54,732 --> 01:31:57,826
- He didn't hesitate.
- He wouldn't hesitate now.

1297
01:31:57,901 --> 01:32:00,233
We did all the fucking work!
Where was he before?

1298
01:32:00,304 --> 01:32:03,330
It doesn't matter.
Erin, will you listen to me?

1299
01:32:03,407 --> 01:32:05,671
You want to win this?
He just gave me this check.

1300
01:32:05,743 --> 01:32:08,507
It covers all
our expenses to date,

1301
01:32:08,579 --> 01:32:12,015
and he's got more
toxic tort experience
than anyone in the state.

1302
01:32:12,082 --> 01:32:14,676
This is good news.

1303
01:32:16,620 --> 01:32:19,589
By the way,
I got Pamela Duncan.

1304
01:32:19,656 --> 01:32:21,590
Hey.

1305
01:32:31,803 --> 01:32:34,670
I'll open, Mommy.

1306
01:32:34,739 --> 01:32:38,140
You want to open
the can for Mommy?
Here, I'll help you.

1307
01:32:38,209 --> 01:32:40,473
Can you turn it?

1308
01:32:40,545 --> 01:32:42,979
[Motorcycle Revving]
[Gasps]
Hi, George.

1309
01:32:43,047 --> 01:32:45,015
Hi, George.
Let's go see.

1310
01:32:45,082 --> 01:32:47,482
[Revving
Continues]
Let's go see.

1311
01:32:53,624 --> 01:32:56,855
[Revving Continues]

1312
01:32:59,697 --> 01:33:04,828
[Motorcycle Departing]

1313
01:33:11,108 --> 01:33:13,668
- Erin Brockovich?
- Yeah.

1314
01:33:13,744 --> 01:33:16,008
Package
from Masry & Vititoe.

1315
01:33:25,756 --> 01:33:29,021
Thank you.
Thank you.

1316
01:33:31,963 --> 01:33:33,897
What's in here?
Baby.

1317
01:33:33,965 --> 01:33:38,868
There's no baby in here.
What is it?
A dolly.

1318
01:33:38,936 --> 01:33:41,200
It's a dolly?
It's...

1319
01:33:53,251 --> 01:33:55,947
Look.

1320
01:33:56,020 --> 01:33:57,954
Look.

1321
01:33:58,022 --> 01:34:00,855
"Look" is right.

1322
01:34:00,925 --> 01:34:03,894
[Gasps]

1323
01:34:07,798 --> 01:34:09,891
Do you see that?
Do you see that?

1324
01:34:12,670 --> 01:34:16,231
I want that.
I want that too.

1325
01:34:16,307 --> 01:34:19,401
It's our lucky day.
Matthew! Katie!

1326
01:34:30,254 --> 01:34:33,883
PG&E has requested
that we submit
to binding arbitration.

1327
01:34:33,958 --> 01:34:35,858
What's that?

1328
01:34:35,927 --> 01:34:40,523
That's where we try
the case without a jury,
just before a judge.

1329
01:34:40,598 --> 01:34:42,532
It's called
a test trial.

1330
01:34:42,600 --> 01:34:45,865
The judge’s decision is final.
There is no appeal.

1331
01:34:45,937 --> 01:34:48,235
How many plaintiffs
do you have?

1332
01:34:48,306 --> 01:34:50,297
Six hundred
and thirty-four.

1333
01:34:50,374 --> 01:34:53,366
They'll never try
that many all at once.

1334
01:34:53,444 --> 01:34:57,210
So we need to get them
together in groups
of 20 or 30;

1335
01:34:57,281 --> 01:35:00,580
worst cases, the most
life-threatened, the sickest
in the first group.

1336
01:35:00,651 --> 01:35:02,585
And so on
and so on.

1337
01:35:02,653 --> 01:35:06,020
Each one gets a go
before the judge
to determine damages.

1338
01:35:06,090 --> 01:35:08,388
PG&E has proposed that
they're liable...

1339
01:35:08,459 --> 01:35:12,395
anywhere between 50
and 400 million.

1340
01:35:12,463 --> 01:35:16,695
So... Wait a minute.
Let me just get this straight...

1341
01:35:16,767 --> 01:35:20,225
If we went to trial,
PG&E could stretch this
over ten years...

1342
01:35:20,304 --> 01:35:22,363
with appeal
after appeal.

1343
01:35:22,440 --> 01:35:25,432
Those people
in Hinkley...
These people
are expecting a trial.

1344
01:35:25,509 --> 01:35:27,374
That's what
we told them.

1345
01:35:27,445 --> 01:35:30,073
They won't understand this.

1346
01:35:31,816 --> 01:35:34,785
Kurt thinks it's
the best way to go.

1347
01:35:43,094 --> 01:35:48,691
[Kurt]
I promise you that we'll be
very sensitive on this point.

1348
01:35:48,766 --> 01:35:54,534
We will make sure that they
understand this is the only way
we can go forward at this time.

1349
01:35:54,605 --> 01:35:57,699
But we have a lot
of work to do...

1350
01:35:57,775 --> 01:36:01,336
before we even broach
that subject.

1351
01:36:02,446 --> 01:36:04,380
Why don't I take Erin
down the hall,

1352
01:36:04,448 --> 01:36:07,975
so we can start on this stuff,
and I'll fill her in on the rest
of the details.

1353
01:36:08,052 --> 01:36:11,146
[Kurt]
Thanks.
Those are my files.

1354
01:36:11,222 --> 01:36:13,713
Yeah, we had them
couriered over.

1355
01:36:13,791 --> 01:36:16,385
Listen, good work.
They're a great start.

1356
01:36:16,460 --> 01:36:20,396
We're just going to have to
spend a little time filling in
the holes in your research.

1357
01:36:20,464 --> 01:36:23,058
Excuse me.
Theresa, is it?

1358
01:36:23,134 --> 01:36:25,432
There are no holes
in my research.

1359
01:36:25,503 --> 01:36:29,269
No offense. There are just
some things we need that you
probably didn't know to ask.

1360
01:36:29,340 --> 01:36:31,740
Don't talk to me
like I'm an idiot, okay?

1361
01:36:31,809 --> 01:36:34,505
I may not have a law degree,
but I've spent 18 months
on this case,

1362
01:36:34,578 --> 01:36:38,014
and I know more about these
plaintiffs than you ever will.

1363
01:36:38,082 --> 01:36:41,609
Erin, you don't even have
phone numbers for some of them.

1364
01:36:41,686 --> 01:36:44,018
Whose number do you need?
[Theresa]
Everyone's.

1365
01:36:44,088 --> 01:36:46,852
This is a lawsuit.
We need to be able
to contact the plaintiffs.

1366
01:36:46,924 --> 01:36:49,324
I said,
"Whose number do you need?"

1367
01:36:49,393 --> 01:36:53,090
You don't know 600 plaintiffs'
numbers by heart.

1368
01:37:07,445 --> 01:37:13,350
- Annabelle Daniels.
- 714-454-9346.

1369
01:37:13,417 --> 01:37:15,942
Ten years old, eleven in May.
Lived on the plume since birth.

1370
01:37:16,020 --> 01:37:17,954
Wanted to be
a synchronized swimmer,

1371
01:37:18,022 --> 01:37:21,651
so she spent every minute
she could in the PG&E pool.

1372
01:37:21,726 --> 01:37:23,887
She had a tumor
on her brain stem
detected last November,

1373
01:37:23,961 --> 01:37:27,158
an operation on Thanksgiving,
shrunk it with radiation
after that.

1374
01:37:27,231 --> 01:37:30,200
Her parents are Ted and Rita.
Ted's got Crohn's disease.

1375
01:37:30,267 --> 01:37:34,328
Rita has chronic headaches
and nausea and underwent
a hysterectomy last fall.

1376
01:37:34,405 --> 01:37:37,169
Ted grew up in Hinkley.
His brother Robbie
and his wife May...

1377
01:37:37,241 --> 01:37:40,677
and their five children...
Robbie, Jr., Martha, Ed,
Rose and Peter...

1378
01:37:40,745 --> 01:37:42,872
also lived
on the plume.

1379
01:37:42,947 --> 01:37:47,384
Their number is 454-9554.
You want their diseases?

1380
01:37:51,822 --> 01:37:54,985
Okay, look, I think we got off
on the wrong foot here.

1381
01:37:55,059 --> 01:37:59,052
That's all you got, lady:
Two wrong feet
and fucking ugly shoes.

1382
01:38:04,668 --> 01:38:06,602
[Erin]
She insulted me.

1383
01:38:06,670 --> 01:38:08,695
Bullshit. It was
a misunderstanding.

1384
01:38:08,773 --> 01:38:12,038
Instead of handling it
politely, instead of
treating her with respect,

1385
01:38:12,109 --> 01:38:14,043
you insult her.
Why the fuck
should I respect her?

1386
01:38:14,111 --> 01:38:16,045
Just because she's not
supporting three kids...

1387
01:38:16,113 --> 01:38:18,377
with no husband
and no education,
doesn't make her an idiot.

1388
01:38:18,449 --> 01:38:20,542
Just because
she dresses like a lawyer,

1389
01:38:20,618 --> 01:38:22,711
doesn't mean she didn't
work her ass off...

1390
01:38:22,787 --> 01:38:24,880
in law school
and shit positions
to earn her way.

1391
01:38:24,955 --> 01:38:27,014
Excuse me
for not going to law school.

1392
01:38:27,091 --> 01:38:30,720
Law school?
I'd settle
for charm school!

1393
01:38:33,931 --> 01:38:37,662
[Cow Mooing]

1394
01:38:37,735 --> 01:38:40,898
Mister... Mister...
Mr. Linwood!

1395
01:38:40,971 --> 01:38:45,305
[Clearing Throat]
Mr. Linwood?

1396
01:38:48,746 --> 01:38:50,814
Bob?

1397
01:38:53,750 --> 01:38:58,187
[Erin Blowing Nose]
6086 Ridge Road,

1398
01:38:58,254 --> 01:39:03,055
[Clears Throat]
Hinkley, California.
714...

1399
01:39:03,126 --> 01:39:06,391
[Sneezes]
455...

1400
01:39:06,462 --> 01:39:10,762
[Theresa]
Okay, now, if you could
walk me through...

1401
01:39:10,834 --> 01:39:13,860
all of the elements of...

1402
01:39:13,937 --> 01:39:16,030
Annabelle's illnesses.

1403
01:39:16,105 --> 01:39:21,372
Specific details,
when the symptoms began...

1404
01:39:21,444 --> 01:39:24,174
prior to the first
medical visit.

1405
01:39:24,247 --> 01:39:29,207
If you could reserve
sentimental embellishments,
I'd appreciate it.

1406
01:39:29,285 --> 01:39:32,015
They're not gonna help you
in court.
All right.

1407
01:39:32,088 --> 01:39:35,353
So I just need facts,
dates... time.

1408
01:39:35,425 --> 01:39:39,623
[Erin] I know Theresa
isn't real warm, but they say
she's a good lawyer.

1409
01:39:39,696 --> 01:39:42,324
[Ted]
She's asking the same
questions you asked.

1410
01:39:42,398 --> 01:39:45,492
I already told you everything.
I don't want her coming
to the house again.

1411
01:39:45,568 --> 01:39:48,662
She's kind of stuck-up,
and she upsets Annabelle.

1412
01:39:48,738 --> 01:39:51,832
If you don't like Theresa,
that's okay.

1413
01:39:51,908 --> 01:39:54,843
You know how important
Annabelle is to me.

1414
01:39:54,911 --> 01:39:57,004
Ed and I are still here
for you.

1415
01:39:57,080 --> 01:40:00,675
I called Ed two days ago,
and he still hasn't
called me back.

1416
01:40:00,750 --> 01:40:06,655
Now I hate to say this,
but... everyone's pretty upset
about this arbitration thing.

1417
01:40:06,723 --> 01:40:08,850
What?

1418
01:40:08,925 --> 01:40:11,223
Pamela's written a letter
in the Hinkley news...

1419
01:40:11,294 --> 01:40:15,390
telling everybody
to get new lawyers,
that we've been lied to.

1420
01:40:15,465 --> 01:40:18,696
Is it true?
No.
[Stammering]

1421
01:40:18,768 --> 01:40:21,862
Did you?
I'm telling you the truth,

1422
01:40:21,938 --> 01:40:24,202
and I will get
to the bottom of all this.

1423
01:40:24,274 --> 01:40:26,208
Don't lie to us.

1424
01:40:26,276 --> 01:40:29,712
I will take care of this.
I promise.
We're trusting you here.

1425
01:40:29,779 --> 01:40:33,408
Thanks.
I'll talk to you soon, okay?
All right. Bye-bye.

1426
01:40:36,419 --> 01:40:39,149
Ed, I'm not saying
it's not a strong case.

1427
01:40:39,222 --> 01:40:42,316
If it wasn't a strong case,
every demurrer wouldn't
have been dismissed.

1428
01:40:42,392 --> 01:40:46,192
I wouldn't be here.
What I am saying
is we still don't have...

1429
01:40:46,262 --> 01:40:49,095
a smoking gun that ties
San Francisco to Hinkley;

1430
01:40:49,165 --> 01:40:52,532
something that proves
that prior to 1987...

1431
01:40:52,602 --> 01:40:57,665
PG&E corporate knew
the water was bad in Hinkley
and did nothing about it.

1432
01:40:57,740 --> 01:41:01,870
[Rosalind]
Hey, Erin, I thought
you were taking a sick day.

1433
01:41:01,945 --> 01:41:03,879
So did I.

1434
01:41:09,118 --> 01:41:12,849
What's going on
in there?
A meeting
about the PG&E thing.

1435
01:41:12,922 --> 01:41:14,981
Are you sure?
Yep.

1436
01:41:17,160 --> 01:41:20,596
[Kurt]
We can find it
or we don't have a big win.

1437
01:41:20,663 --> 01:41:23,860
Can I take a brief break here
for a moment?

1438
01:41:23,933 --> 01:41:25,924
I'll be right back.

1439
01:41:28,371 --> 01:41:32,307
[Arguing, Indistinct]

1440
01:41:32,375 --> 01:41:35,367
[Arguing Continues]

1441
01:41:35,445 --> 01:41:38,642
You told me you weren't feeling
great. I wanted you to rest.
You know, that is bullshit.

1442
01:41:38,715 --> 01:41:40,979
Get in here.
If I was on my deathbed,

1443
01:41:41,050 --> 01:41:43,644
if it helped you,
you'd drag me out of it!

1444
01:41:47,690 --> 01:41:49,817
How could you
take this away from me?

1445
01:41:49,892 --> 01:41:53,828
Nobody's taking anything.
Bullshit!
You stuck me in Siberia...

1446
01:41:53,896 --> 01:41:56,831
dictating to some
goddamn steno clerk...

1447
01:41:56,899 --> 01:41:58,958
so you could
finish this without me!

1448
01:41:59,035 --> 01:42:03,495
They screwed up, Erin!
Do I have your attention now?
They admit it.

1449
01:42:03,573 --> 01:42:07,566
The arbitration proposal
they sent might as well have
been written in Sanskrit...

1450
01:42:07,643 --> 01:42:09,668
for all the sense it made
to the people in Hinkley.

1451
01:42:09,746 --> 01:42:14,274
I know. L-I spoke to Ted.
Pamela Duncan wouldn't even
get on the phone with me!

1452
01:42:14,350 --> 01:42:17,183
Pamela's got everybody
seeing red with that letter
she wrote to the press.

1453
01:42:17,253 --> 01:42:19,187
She called us thieves.
They're all listening
to her.

1454
01:42:19,255 --> 01:42:21,519
The whole thing
is about to fall apart!
Why? Why?

1455
01:42:21,591 --> 01:42:23,684
Before we even go
to arbitration,

1456
01:42:23,760 --> 01:42:25,694
we have to get
the plaintiffs to agree.
How many?

1457
01:42:25,762 --> 01:42:28,526
Usually they're required
to get about 70%.

1458
01:42:28,598 --> 01:42:32,534
PG&E is demanding 90.
In other words, everybody.

1459
01:42:32,602 --> 01:42:34,797
Now do you understand?
This is serious.

1460
01:42:34,871 --> 01:42:37,362
And what?
I'm not serious?

1461
01:42:37,440 --> 01:42:39,635
You're emotional.
You're erratic.

1462
01:42:39,709 --> 01:42:41,643
You say any goddamn thing
that comes into your head.

1463
01:42:41,711 --> 01:42:44,976
You make this personal
and it isn't.
Not personal?

1464
01:42:45,048 --> 01:42:48,984
That is my work, my sweat,
my time away from my kids!

1465
01:42:49,052 --> 01:42:52,146
If that's not personal,
I don't know what is!

1466
01:42:52,221 --> 01:42:56,885
[Coughing]

1467
01:42:56,959 --> 01:43:01,828
Come on.
Come on.

1468
01:43:01,898 --> 01:43:04,662
Go home.
Get well.

1469
01:43:04,734 --> 01:43:07,669
You're no good
to me sick.

1470
01:43:07,737 --> 01:43:10,331
I need you,
all right?

1471
01:43:10,406 --> 01:43:13,341
This case needs you.

1472
01:43:15,244 --> 01:43:17,906
Did you tell them that?

1473
01:43:42,271 --> 01:43:46,207
Binding arbitration
isn't all that different
from a trial.

1474
01:43:46,275 --> 01:43:50,371
It's overseen by a judge,
evidence is presented
in much the same way.

1475
01:43:50,446 --> 01:43:52,505
[Man]
And then a jury decides?
[Coughs]

1476
01:43:52,581 --> 01:43:55,049
Oh, no. Sorry I forgot
to mention that.

1477
01:43:55,117 --> 01:43:58,280
There's no jury
in binding arbitration.
[Crowd Murmuring Loudly]

1478
01:43:58,354 --> 01:44:01,585
- No jury and no appeal.
- [Crowd Continues Murmuring]

1479
01:44:01,657 --> 01:44:04,683
What option do we have
if we don't like the result?

1480
01:44:04,760 --> 01:44:06,955
You have none.
The judge's decision is final.

1481
01:44:07,029 --> 01:44:10,465
Not a good answer.
[Ed] We don't anticipate
that being a problem.

1482
01:44:10,532 --> 01:44:13,057
As I already told you,

1483
01:44:13,135 --> 01:44:17,196
it's definitely between
$50 and $400 million.

1484
01:44:17,272 --> 01:44:19,763
Well, which?
There's a big
difference there.

1485
01:44:19,842 --> 01:44:21,969
I wouldn't like
to speculate at this point.

1486
01:44:22,044 --> 01:44:25,445
[Tom Mumbling]
Well, how does it
get divided?

1487
01:44:25,514 --> 01:44:28,915
- Yeah. Who gets what?
- [Crowd Chattering]

1488
01:44:28,984 --> 01:44:34,718
My medical bills
started two years ago, before
some of the other people here.

1489
01:44:34,790 --> 01:44:38,157
My daughter has been in and out
of hospitals more than his.

1490
01:44:38,227 --> 01:44:40,695
It shouldn't matter
when it started.
[Crowd Agreeing]

1491
01:44:40,763 --> 01:44:44,756
Just a minute, please.
People, listen, please!

1492
01:44:44,833 --> 01:44:47,301
The point we have
to address tonight...

1493
01:44:47,369 --> 01:44:51,601
is getting everyone
to agree that going
binding arbitration...

1494
01:44:51,673 --> 01:44:55,837
is preferable to a trial
that could go on for ten years
before you see any money.

1495
01:44:55,911 --> 01:45:00,075
Maybe some of us want
to wait ten years.

1496
01:45:00,149 --> 01:45:03,482
[Crowd Chattering]

1497
01:45:03,552 --> 01:45:07,079
Everyone has to agree
or no one has a chance.

1498
01:45:07,156 --> 01:45:10,455
Those of you about to leave,
I'd like you to keep
this date in mind:

1499
01:45:10,526 --> 01:45:12,721
1978.

1500
01:45:12,795 --> 01:45:16,060
That's the year
of the Love Canal controversy,

1501
01:45:16,131 --> 01:45:18,656
and those people are still
waiting for their money.

1502
01:45:18,734 --> 01:45:23,433
Think about where you'll be
in 15 or 20 years. Huh?

1503
01:45:23,505 --> 01:45:27,703
[Crowd Murmuring]

1504
01:45:27,776 --> 01:45:32,338
Look, everyone,
is this a big decision?

1505
01:45:32,414 --> 01:45:37,681
Absolutely.
But I do not believe
this is a sellout.

1506
01:45:37,753 --> 01:45:40,950
This is the best shot
at getting everyone
some money now!

1507
01:45:42,891 --> 01:45:45,621
You and I both know...

1508
01:45:45,694 --> 01:45:49,790
there are people in this room
who can't afford to wait...

1509
01:45:49,865 --> 01:45:52,299
to take that chance.

1510
01:45:52,367 --> 01:45:56,098
Are you gonna make them wait?

1511
01:46:02,144 --> 01:46:05,375
So how many
altogether?
[Sighs]

1512
01:46:05,447 --> 01:46:08,382
We got just about everybody
that came here tonight,

1513
01:46:08,450 --> 01:46:11,214
but that still leaves us
about 150 short.

1514
01:46:11,286 --> 01:46:13,379
Oh, shit.

1515
01:46:13,455 --> 01:46:16,549
[Clears Throat]
We'll have to go
door-to-door.

1516
01:46:18,961 --> 01:46:21,395
I gotta go
pick up my kids.

1517
01:46:25,134 --> 01:46:28,399
You need a hand
with that?
No, I got it.

1518
01:46:30,672 --> 01:46:34,972
Hey... you did good.

1519
01:46:36,311 --> 01:46:38,245
We'll see.

1520
01:46:38,313 --> 01:46:40,679
Yeah.

1521
01:47:08,277 --> 01:47:10,541
Hey.
Hey.

1522
01:47:12,781 --> 01:47:14,874
Thanks for coming.

1523
01:47:16,118 --> 01:47:19,053
[Sighs]

1524
01:47:19,121 --> 01:47:21,214
Don't take them anywhere
on your bike, okay?

1525
01:47:21,290 --> 01:47:23,724
I'll give you some money
for a cab if you want
to go somewhere.

1526
01:47:23,792 --> 01:47:26,226
[Chuckles]
I got money.

1527
01:47:26,295 --> 01:47:29,731
So how long
is this gonna take?

1528
01:47:29,798 --> 01:47:33,234
Uh... I don't know.
A few days.

1529
01:47:34,736 --> 01:47:37,000
You got your own room.

1530
01:47:48,417 --> 01:47:51,045
I am really sorry, George.

1531
01:47:52,588 --> 01:47:54,579
Have the kids eaten?

1532
01:47:57,759 --> 01:47:59,693
No.

1533
01:48:20,449 --> 01:48:24,078
(sing)(music) I've wept for those
who suffer long (music)

1534
01:48:25,420 --> 01:48:29,049
(sing)(music) But how I weep
for those who've gone (music)

1535
01:48:30,392 --> 01:48:35,193
(sing)(music) Into rooms of grief
and questioned wrong (music)

1536
01:48:35,264 --> 01:48:37,824
(sing)(music) But keep on killing (music)

1537
01:48:40,902 --> 01:48:44,838
(sing)(music) It's in the soul
to feel such things (music)

1538
01:48:46,041 --> 01:48:50,808
(sing)(music) But weak to watch
without speaking (music)

1539
01:48:50,879 --> 01:48:55,213
(sing)(music) Oh, what mercy
sadness brings (music)

1540
01:48:55,284 --> 01:48:58,219
(sing)(music) If God be willing (music)

1541
01:49:06,828 --> 01:49:11,356
[George]
You want to get some pancakes?
Let's go. Everybody, up.

1542
01:49:11,433 --> 01:49:13,435
Everybody, up today.
All right.

1543
01:49:13,435 --> 01:49:15,403
Everybody, up today.
All right.

1544
01:49:15,470 --> 01:49:17,870
Let's get some pancakes.
[Erin]
What time is it?

1545
01:49:17,939 --> 01:49:21,875
It's early.
I'm gonna take your car
and get some breakfast.

1546
01:49:21,943 --> 01:49:25,242
Mm-hmm.
No, I need my car.

1547
01:49:25,314 --> 01:49:27,714
We'll be back in a minute.

1548
01:49:27,783 --> 01:49:30,547
Okay.
Get some sleep.

1549
01:49:30,619 --> 01:49:33,554
Hey, Matt, buddy.
Let's go.
What?

1550
01:49:33,622 --> 01:49:36,648
Put it down.
Let's go.
I'll be there in a minute.

1551
01:49:38,393 --> 01:49:41,658
Let's go get some
pancakes, girlie.
Come on.

1552
01:49:50,806 --> 01:49:52,831
Baby, don't play with that.

1553
01:49:52,908 --> 01:49:55,638
It took me so long
to get it organized.
Will you put that back?

1554
01:49:55,711 --> 01:49:59,147
Please?
This girl is
the same age as me.

1555
01:50:04,419 --> 01:50:07,855
She's one of the sick people?

1556
01:50:07,923 --> 01:50:12,360
Uh... she is, but...
that's why I'm helping her.

1557
01:50:12,427 --> 01:50:14,759
We'll get her some medicine
and make her feel better.

1558
01:50:14,830 --> 01:50:17,390
Why can't her own mama
help her?

1559
01:50:20,435 --> 01:50:22,562
Because her own mom
is real sick too.

1560
01:50:28,877 --> 01:50:31,471
[Sighs]

1561
01:50:36,218 --> 01:50:39,244
I'll bring you back
some breakfast.

1562
01:50:39,321 --> 01:50:41,846
You want eggs?

1563
01:50:43,892 --> 01:50:45,985
Eggs would be great.

1564
01:50:48,864 --> 01:50:51,162
[Door Closes]

1565
01:50:51,233 --> 01:50:53,827
[Chuckles Softly]

1566
01:50:53,902 --> 01:50:56,666
Eggs would be perfect.

1567
01:52:07,008 --> 01:52:09,841
Hey, Matt.
Hey, Erin,
how are you?

1568
01:52:09,911 --> 01:52:12,778
That's good.

1569
01:52:12,848 --> 01:52:15,749
So, been at this
all day?
Yeah.

1570
01:52:15,817 --> 01:52:18,012
You look tired.
You want some coffee?
I'd love some.

1571
01:52:18,086 --> 01:52:20,987
I'll make
a fresh pot.
Thanks.

1572
01:52:34,102 --> 01:52:37,435
[Men Laughing]

1573
01:52:45,847 --> 01:52:50,341
Hey,
don't I know you?
I don't think so.

1574
01:52:50,418 --> 01:52:53,478
Sure, you were
at the barbecue
in Hinkley...

1575
01:52:53,555 --> 01:52:56,149
and at the town meeting.
Hmm.

1576
01:52:56,224 --> 01:52:58,715
I was watching you.

1577
01:53:00,195 --> 01:53:02,789
I had my eye on you.

1578
01:53:04,366 --> 01:53:07,802
How nice.
Sure, you were talking
to everybody...

1579
01:53:07,869 --> 01:53:10,201
and writing down
a lot of stuff.

1580
01:53:10,272 --> 01:53:12,968
When I saw you,
I said to myself,

1581
01:53:13,041 --> 01:53:16,010
"There's something
about her.

1582
01:53:16,077 --> 01:53:18,637
I really like
that girl."

1583
01:53:20,448 --> 01:53:23,417
Matt, can I get that coffee
to go?
Sure thing.

1584
01:53:26,855 --> 01:53:30,416
I feel like I can talk
to you too.

1585
01:53:30,492 --> 01:53:34,223
Like you're the type
of person I could
say anything to.

1586
01:53:35,997 --> 01:53:38,056
Here you go.
Great.
What do I owe you?

1587
01:53:38,133 --> 01:53:41,591
There's no charge.
Thanks, Matt.

1588
01:53:41,670 --> 01:53:44,662
Well,
nice talking to you.

1589
